    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1933-02-16T19:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1933-02-16T19:00:00-05:00" n="602"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d602">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">704.2123/2: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Peru</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Dearing</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lima</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-02-16T19:00:00-05:00"
                            >February 16, 1933—7 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 8:22 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>87. Referring to Department’s telegram No. 32, February 16, 1 p.m.,
                        Manzanilla<note n="2" xml:id="d602fn2">José Matías Manzanilla, Peruvian
                        Minister for Foreign Affairs.</note> cordially acquiesces. I will arrange
                    details with Lozano.<note n="3" xml:id="d602fn3">Fabio Lozano y Lozano,
                        Colombian Minister in Peru.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Dearing</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
